\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 \strokec2 GETGet System Info\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 https://SITE.sparkmeter.cloud/api/v0/system-info\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec2 This call returns information on the connection between the ThunderCloud server and Meter Application Servers (MAS) connected to it as well as general system information.\
This information is formatted in a list. Since each ThunderCloud instance is currently only connected to one MAS, the list contains only one element.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 \strokec2 Typical use case:
\f1\i0 \strokec2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Check that the MAS is online by retrieving the last sync date between the servers.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0
\f2\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 last_sync_date
\f1\fs24  should never be more than a few minutes old.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

